Sample Answer

ColorImage imageA = new ColorImage();

int width = imageA.getWidth();

int height = imageA.getHeight();

Canvas canvas = new Canvas(width, height);

canvas.add(imageA);




Common Mistakes

Giving access modifiers (private, public) to local variables.
Creating canvas of the wrong dimension.
Forgot to add the image to the canvas object.
Treating add(ColorImage) or add(ColorImage, int, int) as class method of the Canvas class. These are instance method and should be called through a canvas object.


